---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/base.astro';

const TITLE = 'Terms';
const DESCRIPTION =
  'Legal notice for the brand-icons documentation site: publisher, hosting, intellectual property, data and applicable law.';

const lastUpdated = '2026-05-17';
---

<BaseLayout title={`${TITLE} — Brand Icons`} description={DESCRIPTION}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <a
      href="/"
      class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-muted hover:text-accent transition-colors"
    >
      ← Home
    </a>
    <header class="mt-8 border-b border-ink/10 pb-8">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-muted">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">{TITLE}</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink-muted">{DESCRIPTION}</p>
      <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ink-muted">
        Last updated · {lastUpdated}
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-neutral mt-10 max-w-none font-sans text-ink">
      <h2>1. Site publisher</h2>
      <p>
        This website (the <em>“Site”</em>) is published by Bryan Berger, self-employed under
        French <em>micro-entrepreneur</em> status, registered with SIREN <code>838 388 205</code>.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Publication director:</strong> Bryan Berger</li>
        <li><strong>Data protection officer:</strong> Bryan Berger</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact:</strong>
          <a href="mailto:contact@bryanberger.dev">contact@bryanberger.dev</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Hosting</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is hosted by <strong>Scaleway SAS</strong>, a French company with registered
        office at 8 rue de la Ville l'Évêque, 75008 Paris, France — <a
          href="https://www.scaleway.com"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">scaleway.com</a
        >. Static assets are served from Scaleway infrastructure in the European Union
        (region <code>fr-par</code>).
      </p>

      <h2>3. Intellectual property</h2>
      <h3>3.1 Source code</h3>
      <p>
        The source code of the <code>brand-icons</code> project (library, tooling and this
        documentation site) is released under the
        <a href="/resources/license">MIT license</a>. Users are granted permission to use,
        copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and sell copies of the
        software, subject to the conditions stated in that license. The software is
        provided <em>“as is”</em>, without warranty of any kind.
      </p>

      <h3>3.2 Brand assets</h3>
      <p>
        The brand icons, logos, names and trademarks shown on the Site or distributed
        through the library remain the exclusive property of their respective owners.
        Their inclusion is intended for purposes of identification and reference
        (<em>nominative fair use</em>) and does not imply any endorsement, sponsorship or
        affiliation. Brand owners may refer to
        <a href="/resources/brand-owners">Brand owners</a> for the takedown procedure.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Liability</h2>
      <p>
        Bryan Berger makes reasonable efforts to keep information published on the Site
        accurate and up to date but offers no guarantee as to its completeness or
        availability, and disclaims responsibility for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>direct or indirect damage to hardware or software resulting from access to the Site;</li>
        <li>any misuse of information published on the Site;</li>
        <li>content imported or referenced by third parties without authorization.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The publisher reserves the right to remove, at any time and without prior notice,
        any content that violates applicable French law, and to pursue civil or criminal
        action against any person posting illegal, defamatory or infringing material.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Personal data</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is a static documentation website. It <strong>does not collect any
        personal data</strong>, does not require an account, and does not run any
        analytics, tracking or fingerprinting solution. No personal data is stored,
        processed or transmitted to third parties by the Site itself.
      </p>
      <p>
        Requests sent by email (e.g. to <a href="mailto:contact@bryanberger.dev"
          >contact@bryanberger.dev</a
        >) are processed solely to respond to the sender and are not used for any other
        purpose. Under the French
        <em>Loi Informatique et Libertés</em> and the EU <em>GDPR</em>, you may at any
        time request access to, rectification or deletion of any personal data you have
        sent by email, by writing to the same address.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The Site does <strong>not</strong> install any cookie, local storage or similar
        tracking technology for advertising or analytics purposes. The only client-side
        storage used is a single key persisting the user's theme preference (light /
        dark), set locally by the browser and never transmitted to any server.
      </p>

      <h2>7. External links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may contain hyperlinks to third-party websites (brand owners' websites,
        GitHub, package registries, etc.). Bryan Berger has no control over those sites
        and accepts no responsibility for their content, privacy practices or
        availability.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by French law. Any dispute relating to the Site or to
        these terms shall fall under the exclusive jurisdiction of the competent courts
        of Paris, France, subject to any mandatory rule of consumer protection law
        applicable to the user.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For any question relating to this notice, write to
        <a href="mailto:contact@bryanberger.dev">contact@bryanberger.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
